               <note xml:id="d2e1496" n="24"> This is his only
                            appearance in rabbinic literature. He is the son of Abba (70) S-H/M, in
                            vol. 4, p. 311, but he was probably Palestinian, as his title רבי
                            suggests. It is well known that his father spent many years in
                            Palestine. He is not to be identified with Ahi (23) son of Abba (60) B/M
                            (see vol. 4, p. 56),
                    </note>
               <note xml:id="d2e1520" n="25"> His father was a contemporary of the last tannaim,
                            see Introduction 7.4.1.</note>
